content:
The Service Intelligence dashboards contain rich data. But if you want a deeper dive into your data or to create your own visualizations, you can do so in Tableau.

Unlock Hidden Insights with Tableau

With Service Intelligence and Tableau, you can:

Connect Tableau to Service Intelligence data model objects using the built-in Explore in Tableau option in your dashboards.
Analyze your data in near real-time with a live connection to Data Cloud.
Publish new analyses to Tableau Cloud to share with your colleagues.

To use Tableau with Service Intelligence data, the following requirements must be met:

* You must have read permissions for the dataspace definition and access to Data Cloud.
* The Tableau user must have at least an Explorer license and permission to view the data.
* The query must exclusively reference objects that come from the DMO.

To view Service Intelligence Data in Tableau, click Explore in Tableau from the dashboard component you want to explore.
title: Integrating Tableau with Service Cloud Data
